x4freetext: The absolute cross section were obtained by normalizing
to elastic scattering of 6 MeV 3He particles measured
at forward angles up to 30 degr., where the elastic
scattering cross sections deviated at most by 20% from
pure Coulomb scattering.
The targets were made by oxidizing tungsten targets in
an 18O atmosphere with the tungsten targets made by
cathode sputtering on carbon backings. The oxidation
was done by high frequency heating of a tantalum ring
in the vicinity of which the targets were mounted.
During the oxidation the targets became transparent.
The target thickness was measured by the energy loss of
alpha particles from an 241Am source. Total target
thickness was about 100 mu-g/cm2.
